The course includes topics like the relationships among the uses and speakers of various languages in multilingual societies, the relationship between language and social identity, language maintenance and shift, language policy and planning, and language and education, including bilingual education.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to provide an overview of the development of Estonian language in relation to linguistic contacts. Series of lectures and independent research provide an overview of the theoretical viewpoints relating to the linguistic area and language contacts of the Baltic Sea region, sociological periods in Estonia and common characteristics in the vocabulary and grammatical structure of the contact languages.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the students: - have a theoretical overview of areal linguistics; - have become acquainted with specific linguistic developments in the Baltic-Sea area; - have some knowledge of the lexical and structural similarities between Estonian and its contact languages; - have some knowledge of the relationship between language and society and the modern multilingualism in Estonia; - have become acquainted with the principles of strategic language planning; - have become acquainted with the framework documents of developing Estonian language; - know the indicators of language vitality and can analyse the linguistic environments of different countries.
